(2) 50% of one cent shall be levied to support the Independence Bowl Foundation and
the proceeds shall be dedicated and used as provided in present law.
(3) 50% of one cent shall be levied to support the Ark-La-Tex Regional Air Service
Alliance and the proceeds shall be dedicated and used as provided in present law.
Proposed law retains present law.
Present law (R.S. 33:4574.1.1) provides that the levy of an additional tax pursuant to present
law shall be subject to approval by a majority of the electors of Caddo and Bossier parishes
who vote on a proposition authorizing the levy of the tax. Provides that the election on the
question of the levy of the tax shall be held only once at a regularly scheduled statewide
election.
Present law provides that the authority to levy the tax shall terminate on June 30th of the
12th calendar year after the date of the approval of the taxation election held pursuant to
present law however, the authority to levy the tax may be renewed if approved by a majority
of the electors of Caddo and Bossier parishes who vote on a proposition authorizing such
renewal.
Proposed law retains present law.
Present law provides that any election to authorize the renewal shall be called by the bureau
for the purpose of submitting such a proposition to the voters. Provides that the election on
the question of the renewal shall be held only once at a regularly scheduled statewide
election. Further provides that if renewed, the term of renewal shall be as provided in the
proposition authorizing such renewal, not to exceed 12 years.
Proposed law retains present law but removes the requirement that an election on the
question of the renewal of the additional tax shall be held only once.
Proposed law directly benefits the Ark-La-Tex Regional Air Service Alliance (RASA),
Independence Bowl Foundation and Shreveport-Bossier Sports Commission (SBSC).
Effective August 1, 2026.
(Amends R.S. 33:4574.1.1(A)(24)(c)(ii))
